FRANCE: A MAR S A PAR - BUR

messages.message: Hey Russia! What do you think about a classic juggernaut? I'm down for a bounce in Black Sea to start

Hi France!
I think England and France tend to make natural allies, so I'd love to work together this game if you're up for it!
Hello Austria! I think our nations both die very quickly without each other's help, so I'm very interested in being on the same page!
Hey Russia! Any interest in going after Turkey together? I propose we bounce Galicia for mutual safety.

Hi Austria!
How are you today? Would you be down to work with me against Turkey?
Also, would you be okay with a bounce in Gal?
Hi Austria! How do you want to split the Balkans?
Hi Italy, just popping in to say hello!
Greetings Germany! I would like to see a central triple developing between the three of us, as I think it's the best option for all of our nations.
Yes, Austria and Italy are just fine as long as we keep peaceful. I will stay out of Tyrolia and would appreciate if you did as well. Would you be interested in going after Turkey together?
Hey Italy! How do you want to proceed? Would you like to work together against Austria?
A juggernaut sounds great to me! A bounce in Black Sea is good with me
Hello England! Any word from France yet? I'm very interested in having the two of us work together in the midgame
Hey France! We should stay coordinated and share info.

Hello England!
Are you down to have a NAP, with you in Norway and me in Sweden?
Hi Germany! Not much for us to coordinate on immediately, but I'd love to stay in touch as the game progresses. Good luck!
Hello France! I am interested in establishing a DMZ in Piedmont, Gol, and West Med - do you have any interest? I'm also very interested in working together in the midgame!

Hello Germany!
Would you be down to have a NAP between us? I'd be fine with you in Denmark and me in Sweden
Hello Turkey! I think that a very viable option - what are you hearing from Russia? Have you heard from Austria about the Balkans?
Sounds good to me, as long as I see Moscow head south :)

Hi France, how are you doing today?
I think France and Russia can work well together, so let's share information as the game progresses?
Hey England! We should stay coordinated and share information
Hi Germany, I'd love to work together this game if you're up for it! Would you be open to bouncing Russia out of Sweden this first year, and then going for the standard 3-build Germany opening?

Greetings Russia! While our nations aren't usually allied, I believe there's a lot of opportunity for collaboration - particularly in the midgame. Let me know what you hear from Austria and Turkey, and I'll see if I can help you out in any way.
Hey Germany! We should stay coordinated and share information

Hello Italy!
Would you be interested in working with me? Austria and I are bouncing in Gal, so if you work with us we should be able to take down Turkey quickly
For sure! Have you heard anything from Russia yet?
I'll go for Serbia and Greece!
Hi England, that sounds great! How do you want to deal with ENG in spring? Shall we DMZ or bounce? I prefer DMZ but I can bounce if you'd like.
Would you be willing to support me into Rum in the fall?
Russia has told me that the two of you have agreed to a standoff in Galicia - is that true?
Hi Turkey, just popping in to say hello! Let's stay coordinated and share information :)
I will go for Serbia and Greece. I won't contest Rumania.
If you would be down to work with me, I'd like to ask for Rum, as I'd really need to build a unit in Sev to move against Turkey
Yes, that sounds good.
Hey England! I know we're on opposite corners, but we do have a common neighbor in Russia. I'll try to keep you informed as things develop in the east
I'd prefer to DMZ if that's okay with you, and then we can see how the first turn goes. That way you can move Brest to MAO and pick up Iberia.
My one caveat is that Austria is clearly a superior player to Russia - if the two of us fight against Austria and he gets strong, I can't imagine that you and I will survive
You can take Rumania and Bulgaria of course!
Austria has said to me that they want to go for Greece and Serbia this year
Have you guys Dmzed the Black Sea? If so, it might be worth it to arrange a bounce
Hi France! Not much for us to talk about immediately, but let's keep in touch! I think France and Turkey are natural allies
If you're up for it, I could move to Norwegian and convoy an army to Norway, and from there we could pressure Stp and Sweden pretty quickly. It would require you to move Kiel-den though.
Yes, we agreed to that
I'm moving Moscow south
Yes, we should team up with Austria
Yes, I'd be happy to support you into Rum if you need it
Any interest in a DMZ in Tyrolia? I think we all stand to gain a lot by not fighting each other

Are you okay with me convoying an army to Norway? If you leave Stp open, I can use it to help you out with Sweden, and we can potentially work against Germany together. If not, I'll just put it in Edinburgh so you don't have to worry about a convoy to Stp.
Also, would you be interested in Dmzing Prussia and Silesia?
Russia didn't say much yet. He agreed to the Galicia bounce with me. Are you opening North?
Are you sure you're going for Greece? I'd like to keep the Mediterranean secure if possible
Sounds good to me
I also would be open to discussing a larger DMZ if you have any interest there too
France seems friendly enough, but that's the only press I've gotten so far. Would be great to see the two of us work together in the midgame!
Are you going to go east or west?
England wants to convoy to Norway, and that's about all the information I have for you right now
Also, are you planning on attacking Germany or England early on?
Just got a message from Austria saying that he intends to move into Greece in the fall, which makes me think he intends to be aggressive
Any read on Russia? I would love to have an idea about what the Tsar is thinking
I think England is opening North. Heard anything from Italy?
Or next year, depending on what Austria does
He says he plans to open south. Whether that's you or Turkey, I don't know.
I'd love to know if you're planning to allow Russia into Sweden. A strong Russia will be hard for me to deal with if Austria and Russia are united
Fine with me
Hi Germany, great to be on a board with you. I'm certainly open to collaborating with one another. Is there anything you'd like to see from me to start?
I'm wondering whether to side with Russia or Turkey
Just got a message from Germany that made it sound like he intends to move into Burgundy. Let me know if you hear anything interesting and I'll do the same
Russia says he plans to open south, which I suppose means either you or Austria.
I'm bouncing with Turkey in Black Sea
Have you heard anything from Turkey?

I think the best thing you can do to help me is probably to use your fleets to set up the lepanto against Turkey - an army convoy to Tunis in the fall would probably be the best plan, as it would give you a good opportunity to Lepanto into Syria or Smyrna next year
And yes, Russia opening south is bad for me, but I'm confident I can hold him off

Do you have any thoughts on Belgium? I'm not terribly fussed about taking it, but Germany might want it. If he doesn't, would you be willing to support me into it in the fall? That way we'd both get two builds and be in good position to attack Germany in 1902.
Next year, Austria and I would also likely be able to get Bul and Rum from Turkey, so it would be easy for you to get Con and Smyrna
It depends on whether you are opening North or not really.
I'm trying to convince Germany to bounce Russia in Sweden, so hopefully that's a sign that we're not dealing with a strong Russia
Longer-term, I'd also like to offer you a chance to stab Austria later on, which we can work out more when the time comes
By the way, I've gotten some indications that England is looking to focus on Scandinavia - just a heads up!
Any interest in going after Russia together?
What are your plans for A Warsaw? Are you trying to sneak into Galicia?
If you're feeling bold, you could open to Armenia while bouncing Russia in BLA and Austria in Serbia, and then support Austria into Rumania. It'd be the end of Russia pretty quickly.
Sure, I'll move my fleet to Den
Hi Austria, why do you think England is opening North?
I'll support you into Rumania and Sevastopol once I'm in Serbia and Greece, and I think England plans to open North so Russia may be weak enough by 1902 that we can take him on together.
To be honest, I'd rather not have an army in Norway, but I understand why you'd want to have it there, and that if it's being used to help me take Sweden I'm fine with it
What are your plans for Sweden? Have you gotten a sense of what Russia's thinking is?
I would also be interested in know if you know what Austria's plans are. He seems like an aggressive player and I'd be nervous if he thinks he can grab 3 centers in 1901
Also, I just wanted to say that I've heard Italy is planning to attack Turkey or Austria, so you should be free to do whatever you want with Marseilles :)
Then we can contain russia from Sweden
England will probably open North FYI, he told me he does

I'm bouncing with Turkey in Black Sea, so they shouldn't be able to stop you from getting Greece and Serbia, and then next year I'll be able to support you into Bul and move into Rum with the fleet in Sev
One thing that's helpful to know: Italy told me he plans to move against Austria, and I think he's genuine. Italy wants to attack Austria and I think that's great for both of us
Italy seems friendly, by the way.
Italy agreed to peace with me. Will he go West or East do you think?
Are you planning to ally with England or France? If you're interested in attacking England, I could help with that next year
If we work together, I think we should be able to hold Austria to 1 build in 1901
Would you be willing to make a move against him this spring? A move to Tyrolia and Venice would set you up to put pressure on Trieste in the fall
Or next year, once Turkey is almost finished, I can move against England
You will need a second fleet eventually to take on Italy but let's talk about that later, ok? I'm fine letting you into Greece in 1902 if you use it to build a second fleet.
In any event, I'm very interested in working together against Turkey - any idea what their plans are?
Any idea if France will move against Italy? Italy is trying to convince me to help him attack Austria, but I'm not a big fan of an Austria that grows strong so quickly
Are you going to Tunis this year? France didn't ask me for anything so I don't know if you need to worry about him. I'm open to attacking Turkey together if you want to.

If you're interested in this, would you be okay with supporting me to Belgium in the fall? That would allow me to have an army in Scandinavia to pressure Russia, and also gives us each two builds while keeping France on the back foot. Then we can see how France opens and decide how to proceed from there.
That could be quite disastrous for Austria
And I wouldn't be so sure that Russia is opening south. He's not very communicative and I'm a little worried that he's working with Austria
I've heard from Russia that the two of you have arranged a standoff in the Black Sea - do you know if that's true?
Well the only other option is me so I hope they go after Austria or Turkey. Okay let's DMZ ENG
Do you think you'll get Sweden?
I'm trying to convince Italy to Lepanto into Syria or Smyrna once Turkey is finished, and then we could split up Italy's Scs between us
Regarding what you said about the midgame, that sounds great to me - I think a partnership between the two of us could be very powerful
I do want to contain Russia but I'm mostly worried about England
Are you going to ally with Germany or England?
I'm worried about Russia, but hopefully England and Germany won't let him expand too much

I'd also point out that an alliance between England and Germany doesn't tend to make any ground in France, since it can easily stalemate in the MAO, so working with France against me would probably get you stuck at Stp with nowhere to expand.

Also, yes I am planning to head to Tunis - I plan to do the standard Italian opening of:
Rome->Apu
Naples->Ionian
Venice hold
And yes, I'm planning to bounce with Russia in the Black Sea. Austria is very aggressive and I think we need to work together if we want to stop him from grabbing 3 centers this year
Your decision, but I'm just going to say that, unless you're planning to attack Austria, and I can't help you much with that, a lepanto would be better long-term
If you go for Stp I'd be willing to work with Turkey
I think a Lepanto is a strong move, but I'm also concerned that it might trigger an R/T - I'm hoping to see how the situation plays out on the Black Sea first
Are you planning to ally with France or Germany?
I think a Lepanto would work quite well

Also, do you have any sense of what the state of Scandinavia is yet? I get the impression that Russia is opening South, and may be moving the Moscow army south, which would leave Scandinavia open for your taking
I do want to move against England if possible. Would you want to work together on remove England from NWY?
I'm currently leaning towards allying with Italy against Turkey
I've been talking to Austria a bit and he seems to think he's in a strong position. I'm trying to get Italy to open to Tyrolia and Venice to put some pressure on him
Russia says he's opening south, but I don't know which country that means.

In any event, I plan to do the standard Italian opening of:
Rome->Apu
Naples->Ionian
Venice hold
They told me they want to convoy to Norway
Italy seems to be inclined to attack Austria, which I think is great for both of us. I'd suggest using this to your advantage. Perhaps you can convince him to leave Piedmont DMZ
Hi Italy, yes a DMZ sounds great to me. What indications do you have from England that they're going full into scandinavia?
Let me know if there's anything else I can do for you at this point!
I would be willing to help you attack Germany once you've got an army in Norway
So you should definitely open North

Another thought: if you're feeling really bold, you could move Bre-mao, Mar-spa, and Par-bur. That would guarantee you two builds, but would leave you quite open to Germany moving to Bur (especially if you two arrange a bounce there in the spring). The alternative is probably a conservative opening, and you'd still get two builds.
Given how things are shaping up diplomatically, would you be interested in a central triple with Germany? I'm looking for ways for the three of us to work together
I would be willing to help you against either one of them
Are you planning to try to move into Galicia?
What's your relationship with France? Are you comfortable going East?
You know that England is planning the convoy this fall? how did you learn that so quickly?
And FYI - if you can guarantee to me that you'll be fighting Turkey with me, I'd be much more comfortable doing the standard Lepanto
What have you heard from Germany and France?
We'd both need to have armies in Bul and Rum, and then we can hopefully force Gal and Ser
I'm bouncing in Gal right now
What about your army in norway?
Either way, though, I'm happy to use it to help you out with Sweden, so long as you leave it empty afterwards :)
I think Italy's communication with me has been pretty good so far, and so I have a feeling that if he's open to attacking Austria then he's genuine
But I'm open to alternatives if you have a strong preference
I haven't decided what direction I'm going yet, but I'm certainly open to working with you.
West for sure
Do you plan on taking Greece this year?
I would likely be able to help against one of them, or I could help against both if you're planning to attack either one
Or maybe you should wait until 1902 to go after Russia. Your call
(If you do go after Russia I would appreciate knowing so I can coordinate with Turkey, and vice versa if Turkey attacks me)
My initial sense is that Russia is opening south, which will keep them from being a threat to you right off the bat
Longer-term, I'd also like to offer you a chance to stab me later on, which we can work out more when the time comes

I think bouncing Russia out of Sweden also works well for both of us, since it weakens Russia, which is a natural rival for you. That way I can keep focusing on fleets and you can focus on armies. We can then work together against France once Russia is dealt with.
And if you can convince Italy to move into Tyrolia, that would be great for both of us. I'd be concerned that Austria might fall quickly if Italy is aggressive
I understand that you don't want to make enemies with either of them before you've had some Scs, so I won't attack either one of them without you giving the all-clear
Have you heard from Germany? I'm trying to get a sense of what they're thinking
Do you think you'll let Russia into Sweden?
And are you still good with the bounce in the Black Sea? I think it's important for both of us to keep each other honest so we can focus on containing Austria
I've gotten the impression that Austria plans to move Vie-gal and Bud-ser, if that helps your planning.
Just so you're aware, I'm telling Italy and Austria that I want to ally with them to attack you, to make them think that they have a chance to backstab Austria in the midgame

My impression is that France is opening in a way that is friendly to both you and I - I don't expect them to make any moves to threaten either of us this year. We should keep an eye out for an F/G alliance in the midgame though, since I think that could be very problematic for both of us
I'm hoping to DMZ Bur, if that's okay with you?
Okay sounds good to me. I'll see what I can do. How did you hear about Germany's play to Bur?
Does that sound reasonable?
Nothing much from France, and Germany seems friendly enough.
I would be lying if I said I wasn't interested in a central triple - I'm currently trying to negotiate a DMZ in Piedmont with France, and would be very open to a central triple
I heard from England that he's definitely going North. If he is opening North, then I think he'll ally with Germany
I agree, I think Russia doesn't want to work with Turkey
Thanks, yes I should have more information after a couple seasons to decide which direction I want to go.
Is Russia offering you something? He told me he's trying to get you to go after Turkey

By the way, I plan to do the standard Italian opening:

Rome->Apu
Naples->Ionian
Venice hold
Any news from Germany? I know France is a bit concerned about an aggressive Germany, so perhaps you can use that to your advantage in the west
Can we also make sure you don't build too many armies?
(Also, the best thing about Bre-mao, Par-bur, Mar-spa is that if Germany does open to Bur, you can always guarantee you pick up Portugal and Spain, while ensuring that he doesn't pick up Belgium).
I'm trying to convince England to open north against Russia, to hopefully distract him from you. Would be great if you could convince him to stay out of the Channel
In any event, I'm planning to open standard - you should know that Russia and Turkey have both told me they're planning to work together
This way we can try to convince Italy to attack Austria
You could consider allying with Austria?
It sounds like France is leaving the Channel open, so you should be able to focus on Scandinavia if that's something you want to do

My initial impression is that Turkey is much more difficult to dig out of their corner position than Austria is - if the two of us were to work together against Turkey, I'd be more inclined to work with you long-term.
My impression is that Russia will open south, but I've tried to convince Turkey to open against Russia as well. If you guys work together, Russia shouldn't last long.
What have you heard from Germany? I don't think he wants to go East
If Italy moves into Tyr, I don't see how that would help Austria
I think Germany will open West
I'm trying to get Germany to agree to let you into Sweden. Perhaps you can offer him a Baltic Sea DMZ to sweeten the deal

I should clarify that I have no reason to think you're lying about your interest in a central triple - the early Italian threat to Germany is clearly a very poor play, and I'm not doing anything aggressive towards you in any event
Hello?
My orders are going to be Lon-nth, Edi-nwg, Lvp-edi. Does that sound good to you?
Yes

Hi Germany, I'm moving into Bur but I don't have any intention to attack you. I consider it a defensive position for myself. What are your thoughts on England so far? I've heard from other players they want to go north but I have no idea if that's truthful.
I think England is opening North, so Russia probably won't be too strong.
Any idea how things are shaping up in the west? I haven't heard anything about alliances there, but England seems worried about France so you might be able to use that to your advantage
After we go after Turkey, we should try to have me focus on armies and you on fleets. That way we won't be in a position to stab each other.
Let me know if there's anything I can do for you!
We should coordinate a bit, if you and Turkey do decide to work together. I'd prefer for Turkey to open to Armenia, obviously :)
I can help you go into Sweden and then we can ally against England?

messages.message: I'm not sure what your plans are for Greece, but I'm pretty sure Italy is planning to convoy there
Nice, I think we're in a good spot
I'm moving to Sweden, and I'd appreciate if you didn't bounce me
I can help you against England or France next year, whichever one you plan to attack
I think you're in a great position to take Trieste!
Austria can't defend against the attack
I'm getting a bit concerned about the moves England is making - they didn't go for the English Channel, and they moved Liverpool to Edi, meaning they're obviously convoying that army to Norway
I can take Greece on my own if you want to contest Rumania and Black Sea. Russia will probably go for Rumania.
I can help you against England next year, or whichever one you plan to attack
Be careful about Italy moving into Trieste!

It's really unclear to me what France is thinking. The support move to Burgundy is not very friendly to you, and they haven't responded to my messages. I'd be careful if I were you, and it might be worth it to talk to England about fighting France together.
It would be great if you could bounce Russia in Sweden this turn too - they're clearly going south, which is great for you
I'm a bit concerned about the moves that England is making - they didn't go for the English Channel, and they moved Liverpool to Edi, meaning they're obviously convoying that Edi army to Norway
I can take Greece on my own, so you can probably try for Rumania and Black Sea if you want.
Agreed - Russia opened south, which is encouraging. You can take Greece and get two builds this year, and then we can move forward
I'm concerned about Italy. Do you think he'll go for Trieste? If he does I can't help you against Turkey.
Nice! That's a strong opening for us. Do you want to go for Belgium or try for Munich?
Indeed they can't - but if I take Trieste, I have no way of getting a build off of it this year
That would be a suicidal move for me

I'm getting a bit concerned about the moves that England is making - they didn't go for the English Channel, and they moved Liverpool to Edi, meaning they're obviously convoying that Edi army to Norway
Glad to see you open south. I'm worried about a possible Lepanto from Italy, so if you could try to convince him to move into Trieste that would be helpful
We should definitely be very careful with the triple alliance between England, France, and Germany
Do you want to bounce in the Black Sea again?

I'll take it as a yes if you don't respond? ;)

In any event, my hope is that you'd be open to continuing the DMZ - that will give you freedom to focus on the north and me freedom to focus on the east!
Yep, that's the plan!
I think it's almost definitely a move to Trieste, since I told them they should Lepanto against Turkey with you and I
Great start for you! I think you're in a great position to dominate Scandinavia
I've heard from other players that Englnad wants to convoy to Nwy but I'm not sure if that's accurate.
I'm trying to figure out what England is planning, but it seems they mainly want to go to Norway atm
Ooh, interesting that Italy didn't move Venice. Are you worried about a possible stab?
If you can get Germany to bounce Russia in Sweden that would be great. I think a weak Russia is good for both of us
I think we need to move our fleets into the Mediterranean, and I can use Sev to move into Rum, so we can get those armies in there
I'm a bit worried about Italy so I may need to cover Trieste. I hope he's not planning to attack me.
So I think this turn we should leave Black Sea Dmz'ed
Have you talked to Italy much? I'd appreciate any information you can give me.

Nice opening for you as well!

Do you think you and Austria will be able to deny Russia Rumania this turn? It would certainly help me out.
Great start for you! You're in a great position to get 2 centers and potentially deny Belgium from Germany
It looks like France is either working closely with Germany or doesn't know what they're doing - the support move into Burgundy is baffling to me. Do you have any sense of what they're thinking?
Could you leave Gal Dmz'ed this turn? I'd like to move War north to deal with that triple alliance between England, France, and Germany
Yes I want to continue the DMZ. I have heard very little from Germany, they wanted to DMZ Bur but I declined.
Nice opening for you - Austria probably won't cover Trieste, if you're feeling risky!
Are you planning to let Russia into Sweden? I think a weak Russia is good for both of us
What's your relationship with Italy?
I think you have a good chance of denying France or England Belgium this turn, and then you should be in a good position to get it next year
If you move North Sea to Ska, and build another fleet in London, you could take Denmark from Germany next year
Nice opening for us! I'm going to go for Belgium this turn. I'd also ask that you bounce Russia out of Sweden, which helps keep Russia weak, and gives you more of a chance of picking it up next year.
Yes, I'm also worried about france
I am a little bit. I think I will need to cover Trieste just in case.

I'd definitely be concerned about the possibility of a triple, especially in light of the way that France has opened. It's also worth noting that it seems that Germany has very little grasp on what they're doing - they offered a DMZ in Burgundy and have now supported themselves in
Do you think you could support me to Belgium with Ruhr?
Will you convoy into Norway? I'm trying to figure out what's happening in the East and I'd appreciate any info you can give me.
If you could try to convince Italy to attack Trieste that would be great for me
If you let me take Sweden, I'll be able to build in Stp and help you against England next year
That's my sense of it too, looks like potentially a convoy to Nwy here. What are you thinking about Bel?
Given that they opened MAO and Bur, it seems likely they are working with England
Are you going to convoy to Tunis this year?
Also, if you could try to convince Italy to attack Trieste, that would be helpful for me. If I have to deal with a Lepanto then I won't be able to attack Russia as effectively
I'm convoying Apu-tun and holding Venice, and planning to build a fleet in Naples - I trust that you're planning to support yourself into Greece? That way, we'll have a solid attack on Turkey in 1902
I think I'm going to take Norway with the fleet instead, to reduce tensions. That way you can feel a bit more safe about not building in Stp :)
We could bounce in Bel?
I'm a bit worried about Italy. He said he won't attack me but I have to cover Trieste just in case. I'd appreciate any info you can give me about him and whether you'll contest Rumania.
I don't think I will try for Mun. I might try for Bel. What are your thoughts? Are you convoying to Nwy?
For what it's worth, I'd like to keep my involvement in the West as much as possible in the midgame, so let me know if you have any interest in doing anything together!
What have you heard from Germany? Do you think he's going to bounce Russia out of Sweden?
Sounds good to me

Right now it looks like there's a triple alliance between England, France, and you, and I'd like to let you know that that is very risky, since England and France are in a perfect position to backstab you

FYI, I'm going to try for Belgium this turn. I've hinted to Germany that I might move there, so I might get his support there, or at least keep him from supporting himself to Belgium. I'd ask that you not bounce me there, but I don't know if you'll see this in time.
I hope you are convoying to Norway
If you could offer to support Germany into Sweden next year, that would also be helpful
What are you thinking for this turn? Will you still be trying for the Black Sea? It looks like you have an opportunity to either get a fleet into Rumania or bounce Turkey again
Would you be fine with that?
I'm trying to get France to move to Munich - I hope he does! That'd be pretty funny :P
I am not working with them. The Burgundy move was very aggressive against me

I'm a bit surprised that you were able to get into Burgundy so easily - are you planning to target Germany first? If you do, I would be willing to use my western armies to support you - I would be open to doing something like moving my army to Tyrolia in the next year if you can guarantee that you're on board with the DMZ.
A bounce is fine with me. Or one of us can take it if we want to start working together.
Did you see my message
I could use your help after Sweden for sure, since I do think England and France are working together
I'm trying to convince Austria to let me have Rum, so I can move my armies north against the triple alliance, since I'd like to move my fleet into Rum
That would also limit Russia to 1 build, and make him an easier target for both of us

I think I'm going to support myself to Greece, sorry. You should still move to Black Sea and contest Rumania. I'm very open to helping you against Russia in 1902, though, so I'd appreciate if you don't contest Greece.
I'm telling Italy that I'm worried about the triple alliance in the north, which is true, so I need those units north
Any idea what Italy is planning? Italy told me he's not moving against Austria, which would be great for both of us, but I'm worried about a possible Lepanto

FYI - Turkey is pushing me pretty hard to take Trieste. I've told them no, but I would expect that they're going to be trying to turn you against me. I do think the IA is much more powerful than the RT, and I'm committed to our alliance
I need to cover for France attacking me

Turkey tells me you plan to convoy into Greece. I'm going to support myself in, but I would appreciate it if you don't move to Trieste. I'd like to move Vienna-trieste just in case you do, but if you don't attack me I'll be much happier.
What are you planning to do with your army in Vienna? It might be wise to cover Trieste just in case
Are you going for Belgium or Munich?
Maybe we can bounce in Belgium instead?
What are you thinking for this turn? Are you planning to try for Greece?
I have a bounce in right now, let me know if you want to work something out for one of us to have it. England also wants it I think.
Are we good?
I'm going to try to move into Greece to stop Austria from getting 2 builds, which would make it even easier for you to take Trieste
Also, I have a feeling that Russia is worried about an F/E/G triple, so you should know that they're definitely going to be doing everything in their power to split the three of you apart
Germany wants me to bounce them in Bel.
By the way, I would be extremely wary of a E/F alliance - once England convoys that army into Norway, they have the advantage of being able to move into Hel or Ska and really grind you down
Have you heard much from France or Germany this turn?
Okay, England was asking me to support them into Bel instead. But I'm going to bounce there.
Is Austria also on board with the R/I/A alliance against Turkey?
I was guaranteed into Bur with that play, why did it surprise you that I got in?
And if you could build a fleet in Marseilles that would be really helpful

In any event, let me know if there's anything I can do for you - the F/E alliance is incredibly dangerous for both of us, so I want to be in a position where I can support you if the E/F starts rolling

You might be able to convince Germany to support you into Belgium, but then he'd probably want you to build in Paris and Brest. It would probably be a better option for you to build in Brest to keep England honest
Okay, let's bounce and we can figure it out next year.
Hello?

Also, I want to confirm that I fully intend to continue to honor our DMZ - it looks like you're going to have your hands full with England and Germany for the foreseeable future, and I don't have any reason to want to start a war with you.
It looks like Germany might be getting three builds this turn, so you might also want to talk to England about going for Belgium
Italy and I have a DMZ going. There is going to be a bounce in Bel.
Hey! Did you figure things out with italy?
It looks like you might be able to pick up 3 builds this turn - that would be great!
Ok I'm going to cover Trieste. Please don't take it personally, I just don't want to get caught in a bad spot if you are just trying to stab me.
Thanks, yes the west is developing slowly, what is your take on the east so far?

Turkey wants me to work against you, but I don't want to. If you don't build in Stp, I'll be much more inclined to work with you than him. I think Turkey and Austria are pretty close, so if you don't build in Stp, I'm happy to work together.

At the moment, I'm planning to convoy to Tunis and hold Venice - I would ideally like to get Austria a bit more entangled with Russia before hitting them, and I think that will be easier to do if you bounce them in Greece
I'll be able to help you into Rumania next year. I think England is going to convoy into Norway so Russia won't get any builds.
Have you heard much from Germany this turn? I'm trying to convince him to bounce Russia out of Sweden, but I haven't heard much back.
If there's anything I can do to support you, please let me know

I'm trying to convince Germany to bounce Russia out of Sweden - I think Austria and Turkey are very friendly, so Russia is in even more trouble if Germany does it. I think if Russia falls fast, we can pick Germany apart pretty easily.
I doubt it, but perhaps we can work together in the next year on France?

messages.message: Well, that's an F/G/R triple :(
Are you still willing to attack Austria? I think you can definitely make progress this year if you convoy to Albania or move into Tyrolia

How are you feeling about the situation? Would you be able to move Gre-aeg and I move Ion-eastern Med this turn? I could then convoy an army into Syria in the fall. It would be ideal if you could move your fleet into Greece behind the army, and that way we have a solid line of units against Turkey
Are you going to try the Lepanto?

I built a fleet in Smyrna because it's my only way of defending against a possible Lepanto. If you're still willing to work with me against Austria, I'll be willing to focus on defending against Russia instead

Russia's northern fleet is really bad for me - it means I'm likely going to lose Norway this year, but I should be able to keep France and Germany out of the English Channel and the North Sea. Hopefully that means I can play them against each other while you and Austria eat up the south.
Would you like to work together against England?

That's definitely an option, but I think that I need to do something like that in the fall - it doesn't do me any good to move to Tyrolia in the spring and then piss off Austria. Are you planning to move to Aeg this turn? I could move to either Albania or Adriatic and we could have a very strong attack against Austria
Yeah I can do that. Do you think I should support myself into Tyrolia? I'm worried about Germany and France.
I'm worried about the possibility of a strong Russia. If he takes me out quickly he's in a great position to continue moving west

Well, that's an F/G/R triple :(

I'm going to keep Germany and France out of the North Sea and the English Channel - hopefully that means I can hold them off while you and Italy eat up the south.
I think you should convince England to help you against Russia, because Russia is clearly targeting Norway
Would you like to work together against England? If you attack North Sea, I can take Norway this turn

I agree - I'm trying to coordinate a move against Turkey with Austria. In any event, I think the F/G is still manageable. I can do whatever I can to help you out diplomatically, and I will try to pass along anything I can learn
Would you be fine with that?
What are your plans this year?

France's builds indicate that they're moving against Germany, and the German bounce in Bel would have France rather suspicious anyway. I don't think you have to worry too much about Germany allying with Russia
Not sure what your plans are for this year, but I think you have a great chance to get into the English Channel this year, since England has to focus on Russia in the north

I think you and Italy have to move quickly if you're going to get Turkey and the Balkans. I'll be taking a major hit this year, but I think you and Italy have a strong alliance, so I think you can eat up the south before it's too late for me :)
Also, if you can let me know if you hear about what Italy is planning to do, I'd appreciate it. I'm worried about a possible Lepanto

What are your plans with the armies? It might make sense for me to convoy Tun-alb if that works for you, so that I have a unit in the area to support you and/or help to defend against a Turkish move to Serbia
I'm very worried about Italy and Austria now, it looks like it's a Lepanto against you
Yes, that sounds good
I might be able to support Germany to Sweden this turn, on the off chance that it helps your alliance.
I'm open to it if Germany is on board, what have you heard from the German?
So I think we need to work together against them
So, it's F/G/R, or I can support Germany to Sweden. I don't think you've got much to gain by keeping me around, but up to you!
Any thoughts for this turn? Are you planning to go for the Black Sea?
It looks like Turkey has to choose between defending Bulgaria or the Black Sea
What do you have in mind?
I appreciate it. I'm talking to Italy now and I think we can do alright. I'll see what I can do to get him to move West.
I'll be spending this turn trying to defend myself against you and France, so it's up to you if you want to have your ally gain any builds this year.
Russia wants to take out England, what are your thoughts on that and working together with R to do that?
If you move into the Black Sea this turn, I won't be able to defend Bulgaria next turn
Can you support him to Sweden?
I'm planning on moving Sev to Black Sea with support from Rum
Oof. Any chance I can convince you to change your mind? I think you're going to get very little out of the alliance with Germany, and Russia is going to take most of my centers.
This would be a great opportunity for you to move Ionian Sea to Eastern Med, and Naples to Ionian Sea, and set up a convoy to Syria next turn
Germany didn't bounce R, looks like GR is friendly. What are your thoughts here?
Do you have any idea what Austria is planning? I'm really worried about the possibility of a strong A/R

It's a shame that England bounced you in Belgium - are you planning to work with France against England? I think that if you coordinate with them, you could easily take the North Sea and the English centers
What do you plan to do? Are you going to try to take Black Sea? I could support Ukraine-rumania and we can support me into Bulgaria in the fall.
Where do you plan to move your fleets?
It would be good for us to work together, but I'm very concerned about your build in Sevastopol
I need Russia's help against England and France though
Great work on the double-fleet build! It looks like you're planning to work with Germany against England? Is there anything that I can do to help out?
Would you be fine if I took Norway this turn? I want to make it look like I'm attacking you, while in reality I can help you against Germany or France
I can try to convince Germany to give you Belgium
Why do you think I've allied with GR? I haven't made any commitments to anyone yet.
I want to work with you, but I think the moves I'm making now are in your best interests, since you can't do much against me in the north anyway
Sounds good to me.
Russia is in a really good position right now, and you shouldn't let him get too strong
I'm worried about Russia in the long term. Are you planning to help him against England?
Also, I'm pretty sure Austria is allied with Russia. If Austria successfully attacks me, you'll likely be next, because you're the only way Austria can expand
I think I'm going to try to take the Black Sea with support from Rum, since I want to keep the army in Ukraine around to move north
I need to figure out if I'm working with Germany or France here. If you can convince Germany to give me Bel that would make my decision easier.
I do, but I'm wondering what to do long term
An R/A alliance is bad for both of us, since Austria will be focused on going after me first, and then Russia will just turn on Austria for the rest of the game
If Russia gets to strong that's a problem for both of us.
My fleet London is going to the English Channel, so please bounce it there. I think we can still work together against Germany, and I'd prefer to do that than let Germany get a dominant position.
Actually I'll attack Bulgaria now to cut any potential support
I think you have a really strong chance to attack Italy this year. Italy told me that he's planning to move to Tyrolia this turn, so you'd be able to take Venice if you move into Tyrolia
I didn't do a double fleet build. I did one army and one fleet.
I haven't heard much from Germany, but what I have heard from them is that they want to work with you against England
Russia is also clearly going after Norway, so he'd be leaving Warsaw and Moscow empty. If you move to Galicia, you'd be in a great position to take Warsaw
I think there's a good chance Austria attacks you this turn, by the way.
If you go for Eastern Med, Turkey can't stop both of us, since Turkey needs to defend Bulgaria this turn and also move Smyrna to the Aegean Sea

I'm willing to support you into Serbia from Rumania if you're willing to work with me, but I'd need to see you make a move against Austria before I can believe that you're actually willing to work with me
I'll probably lose Norway this turn, but if we work together, I think we can get you Belgium this year, and you can pick up the rest of Germany's centers fairly easily.
What do you think we should do?
I'm going to move to Aegean Sea to bounce Turkey and I'm moving to Albania so I can convoy into Turkey or move back into Greece.
The real threat is an R/A/I alliance, which is just as bad for you as it is for me

Your fleet in Stp is really bad for me - it means I can't defend the North Sea from France and Germany, so they're going to take all my home centers before you can take Norway. If you take Norway, you lose Sweden. I don't know what else I can say to convince you that it's not in your interests to take Norway :(

Austria and Russia clearly want to eliminate me because I control the Black Sea, and you're next in line if Austria and Russia defeat me. You're a natural ally to Austria, and if they defeat me then you'll definitely be the next target. You have a lot to gain from working with me
Do you mind if I take Bel to put down another fleet then?
I think I might be able to hold off both of them this year, though. It's going to be hard to come back from this position, but I might be able to play them off each other enough to survive.

I really think you have a lot to gain from working with me against Austria, since you won't get a better chance at taking Austrian centers than you do right now. Austria's also left himself really vulnerable to an attack from you right now
If you'd like I could move Mun-Sil? and we can threaten War
Are you fine with that?
Does that sound good?
What are you planning to do with your army in Spain? If you could move it to Marseilles, it would be really helpful for me
I'm going to bounce you in Aegean but I'm open to working together next turn if you let me keep Greece
If you're willing to work with me against Austria, I'm also willing to retreat out of the Black Sea
I don't want that though. It would be nice not to worry about Bur, however
I haven't heard much from the eastern powers. I don't know what they're going to do. But it looks like an AR, at least that's what R is hoping for.
If Austria moves north and you keep attacking Turkey, I think you're both in really good shape to win the game :)
Why are you worried about Bur? It can't do anything against you.
So Russia would like me to help with Nwy. Any plans to come back from that?
Just so you know, France told me that he's planning to move into the English Channel this turn
I am planning to convoy to Albania and move Naples to Apulia - that way I can keep my options open while still being able to backfill Ionian if needed. I am coordinating with Austria to attack Turkey
Okay, let's see what happens. I'm not sure what to expect from GR here.
If I can free Mun, then I can use it to threaten Russia.
don't you want R to help us v England though?

Sorry I didn't get a chance to respond last turn.

I don't have much chance of coming back if you and France keep attacking me, but if I guess wrong, I might be eliminated by the end of the year. I don't think that's in your interests though - France is going to get most of my centers, and Russia's not in position to do much for you.

messages.message: Damn, those moves weren't great for you.

It's a shame that you were planning on attacking me instead of Russia, since Russia's going to get a lot of my centers before you do. You really have a lot to gain from working with me instead of Russia, especially since I can still help you against Russia
Ok I'm committed to attacking Italy now that I know he's stabbing me. Please let me keep Greece.
Why didn't you retreat to Ska? I'm going to support hold Norway, so you can't take it back
Can you support Austria into Bulgaria this turn? I think that that attack will be guaranteed, and that way Turkey will be forced to disband. We're then in a good spot to deal with Austria.

Is Austria attacking you, or moving north to attack Germany? I'm not clear to me what's going on.

If you need any help, I can put pressure on Austria by sending a message. I think you should be able to talk Turkey into supporting your army from Tunis to Greece, or something along those lines.
I didn't trust you before
I think that would work, yes
I think it's okay - I'm trying to get Russia to work with me, and I think I can still get Austria to support me into Turkey

Because that lets Germany into the North Sea, which is much worse for me. I'm not going to be getting any builds while you and Germany will, so it makes more sense for me to just delay your gains while Germany gets into better position.
If you're willing to work with me, I'm willing to let you keep Greece, but I'd need to see you attacking Russia this turn

I also don't have much reason to lie to you at this point, so I'd rather just tell the truth than try to pretend otherwise.

What I can offer you is an alliance against Germany - I think France would join in, because otherwise Germany is going to get all the builds.
Sorry about the bounce in Albania - should I support you into Aegean this turn?
I'm not going to let you take Norway back, because I think that would cause more damage to me, but I'd be happy to work with you in the future if you stay alive
Can you support me to Bulgaria?

France's moves this turn show that he's not interested in working with you. I think you should convince Germany to help you against Russia. If you can get Germany to tap Sweden, you'll be able to take Norway back from Russia
Also, if you could move to Wales this turn, you'll be able to defend against a possible French attack. If France moves to the Irish Sea this turn, you'll still be able to defend Liverpool next year
Why did you move to Apulia and convoy to Albania? That seems like a really obvious stab.

I think I'm better off just delaying their progress while Austria attacks Russia, and Italy gets better position against Austria.

What do you think about the possibility of supporting Italy's army Tunis to Greece?
Yes, I can support you into Bulgaria
I thought you were okay with me taking Bel here.
I'll use Rumania to support Serbia to Bulgaria, and I'll use Black Sea to attack Con

I'm not really sure what you're planning for this turn, but it would be helpful to me if you could convince Germany to go after Russia instead of you. Russia is clearly targeting England's centers, and you'll need German help if you want to take England's centers
I'm moving to Piedmont to threaten Marseilles

I'm willing to support you to Belgium this turn, if you let me know which army you're moving. If you're interested in working together, I can give you support there, and I can hold off the Germans while you and Russia take the rest of my centers.
I was not, and I said so
Norway is going to support Hel to North Sea

Also, it would be really helpful for me if you could tell me what Italy is planning to do this turn. He's been really slow to respond to my messages, and I'd really appreciate it if you could convince him to work with me instead of Austria.
That way you are guaranteed to take the North Sea, and England can't take back Norway
However, R is getting too strong and I need to reconsider some options.

To be clear, I think you're better off working with me than allying with Germany - Germany is much less likely to let you get anything out of the alliance than I am, and you need an ally in the north to have any chance of holding your corner of the board.

Alright, this isn't great for either of us. Russia is going to take Bulgaria from you, which is guaranteed. However, I think I can get Austria to move Greece-aegean again. I can support them into the Aegean, and then you can support my fleet from Ionian into Greece, taking the center and crippling Austria's position.

If I can convince Austria to go for the Aegean, that will leave them exposed and give us a chance to beat them.
What do you think about sending MAO to Irish Sea?

Are you still willing to work with me against Austria? You're in a really good position to attack Austria this turn, and Austria has left his home centers really vulnerable to you. If you work with me, we can both benefit from Austria's centers
You'll be able to take the channel this turn, which is great - are you planning to go for Irish Sea as well? That would give you a good shot at Liverpool
As long as you keep supporting Austria, Austria will always be in a better position to stab you than you are to stab Austria
Thanks, I'm moving to Hel-Nth

I think you can hold off Russia and Austria in the south for at least a year or two if Italy joins you in the south, and if Italy's position is good enough that he can fight Austria, then it won't matter that Russia has all the builds from your centers.
It's likely that England won't be able to take Norway back, so that English fleet will be stuck there
If you move to the Aegean Sea again and support Tunis to Greece, you should be in a good enough position to hold the position for at least a few years, if Italy helps.
That would be really helpful for me if you could convince Austria to move to the Aegean. I'm still willing to support you into Greece this turn if you're willing to work with me
You should also move Armenia -> Ankara this turn.
Okay, I didn't understand that's what you meant.
Is there anything that I can do to help out?
The problem is that I want to work with you, but I also need to make sure I can defend myself from you, so that's why I can't work with you this turn

Once Austria gets my home centers, your position will be much weaker than Austria's. It will be much easier for Austria to stab you once he's grown a little bit larger than you, and he'll be in a much better position to take Italian centers than you are to take Turkish centers

I'm supporting Greece into Aegean this turn, so hopefully Austria will take Bulgaria. If you work with Austria, you will be able to take Bulgaria this turn, and then we will be in a good spot to take centers from Turkey next year
I'm going to lose Greece this year but next year I'll support you into Con and Ankara
I'm sorry
If you're willing to work with me, I'm willing to use my army in Bulgaria to help you attack Austria, so you don't need to worry about Austria taking Rumania from you
Okay, can you support Bur-Bel? I'll do what I can to help you.
I'll also use Black Sea to attack Con, which will cut support to Bulgaria and allow Austria to take it
This doesn't look good for you. Do you think you can convince one of France or Germany to side with you?
While I'm not a position yet to do anything about Russia, I am considering a change for next year.
Maybe offer to support France into Belgium this turn? That will slow down their attack, and hopefully they'll be too preoccupied with Germany to come after you too hard
I heard Austria is moving to Pie, is that correct?
I'm still trying to work with you - I don't want to have to work with Turkey. Do you want support into the Aegean this turn?

I'm probably not going to survive much longer, but I think we'd be better off working together than fighting each other. I don't have anything else to offer though - I'm just going to try to defend the North Sea as long as possible.
What do you think?
I'm concerned about Germany. They also keep saying they want to send an army at you. They said I could have Bel then moved into it.
I'm also trying to convince France to go after German centers instead of you, so hopefully that would help you convince Germany to help you out
Do you think you can convince England to help you against France?
Russia is going to help me in to the North sea
I don't think so - neither of them are very interested in working with me.
Hopefully we can work together in the future though

I think I'm just better off delaying their progress while you and Italy take out Turkey, and you attack Germany with Russia.

I can't do much else though - if France and Germany keep attacking me, then it's just a matter of time until they both grow stronger than me. I can't offer Russia anything in return for an alliance, but I think France would go along.
Also, you're in a good spot to make a move against Germany, especially with Austria's army in Tyrolia - are you planning to move to Ruhr? You'd be able to take Munich next year
I think you still have a chance of surviving though, and I'll try to help you out next year
It looks like you're attacking England? What are you doing with your fleets? Do you think you could attack Italy?
can you tap Hol so I can take Bel?
I think you'd have a better chance of taking French centers than you would taking English ones.
I'll also let you keep the Black Sea if you support my army in Bulgaria to hold this turn
I need some sort of explanation
Make sure to also support Hel to North Sea using Denmark, or the move won't work
Hopefully I can convince them to move Gre-aegean, and if that works out, I think we're in a good spot to take centers from Austria next year
Please let me know in the next minute or I will reverse my orders.
I think I'd much rather support Burgundy to Belgium than Picardy to Belgium, if you're willing.

Even if you're not planning on working with me, it would be helpful if you could not attack Bulgaria. If you attack Bulgaria, it will likely be successful, but it will also help Russia grow a lot faster than you if you continue to work with him
Also, are you going to try to take the English Channel again this turn?
I'm not going to attack Italy
Can you offer to support Russia to Denmark?
I'm doing what I can to convince Turkey to work with you, but I don't know if he'll bite.

There's no way for you to gain any of my centers this turn, and Austria's in a much better position to stab you than you are to stab Austria. If you continue to work with Austria, your growth will be slow at best, and you'll be in a much worse position than you would be if you stab Austria this turn
You may be right. I'm not sure how I could help you at this point though?

With England and Germany occupied with fighting, I think we can work out a nice I/F/R alliance for the endgame. Once you're able to stab Germany, I think you'll be able to pick up German centers really quickly, especially as they move east to defend against Russia.
Is there anything I can do to help you on my end? I'd much rather have you and Turkey around, since Turkey can actually help you both fight the Austria-russia alliance.
Are you fine with not attacking me in Sevastopol, and Black Sea? I want to move Ukraine to cover it in case you decide to move Armenia to Sevastopol
Once Austria takes Bulgaria and/or the Aegean Sea, it will be much easier for Austria to take my centers than it will be for you
I really need help against Italy
You can't take Nwy
I'm not sure about Austria - I'm going to ask them about their plans
It would also be helpful for me if you could tell me if you think Austria is willing to work with me, since I haven't been able to get Austria to stab Russia
it won't work that way, you have to tap Hol

I'm going to ask Austria about their plans this turn, and I'll let you know if I think I can get them to move Gre-aegean. If I'm able to get that to happen, I'll suggest that you support me into Greece, and then we can be in a good position to attack Austria
I think they're amenable but both of us are not in a good position atm
to work against R

messages.message: If you don't try to work with Italy here, I think you're going to get taken out by Russia and Austria working together.
I'm sorry about moving to Piedmont but I have to attack Italy now
Well I guess I have to work with Turkey now, unless you have a good plan

I have been trying to work with Italy all game, and he's just been ignoring my messages. It would be a lot easier for me to defend against Russia and Austria if Italy would respond to my messages, and he hasn't been doing that. He's been slow to respond, and I need him to actually respond to my messages
Can you support Bulgaria to hold?
This turn I'm going to try to take Armenia

That fleet in Berlin is interesting. If you want to attack Russia, I'm willing to help you - I'm not really in a position to do much else at this point.

If you don't want to attack Russia, then I'm going to try to convince France to work with me, which should make your life a little more difficult.
Oof, we didn't get Nth
At least I tried to support you into Aegean
Yes, I can support Bulgaria
The results would've likely been better for you, but I'm willing to let bygones be bygones if you're willing to stab Austria
You could have let me know.
If you move the fleet to the Baltic Sea, I think we have a good chance of getting you Sweden this year.
You have no reason to trust me but I'm not attacking you anymore. I have to deal with Italy.
Exactly my plan!
It's unfortunate, but we will still be able to take the North Sea eventually

I have messages going out to both Austria and Russia, and I think they're actually pretty close to attacking each other. Austria is the stronger player, and would probably be willing to stab Russia after one of you is eliminated, or at least stop giving Russia the Black Sea, which would be a big deal for you.
Why are you supporting Austria into centers? I'm in a good spot to work with you and Turkey, but I need you to help me out here - I need to know if you are working with me or Austria.
You were the one who stabbed me
This turn I'm using Norway to support Hel to North Sea again

I still want to work with you, but if you continue to work with Austria, that's going to put us in a really tough spot. You and I will be in a much better spot to take centers from Austria, and then we can take centers from Turkey. I think that you and I have much more to gain from working together than you and Austria do
We can still work together if you want to but I need you to stop helping Turkey
I'm not planning on working with Italy against you. My main focus now is just to defend against Russia
I think if you move to Greece this turn, Turkey would be willing to support you.

Can you support Turkey into Bulgaria this turn? You and Turkey will still be in a good spot to attack Austria. However, if you and Austria continue to work together, Turkey and I will be forced to work together, and we won't be able to beat Austria
If you don't tap any of my units this turn, I can defend against Russia
I'm sorry, but I need to work with Austria here

Or the other way around, if you move to Greece with Turkey's support.

messages.message: I wish France had actually responded to my messages.
I'm not going to be able to move any units to help you this turn, so you should convoy to Albania
Can you tap Piedmont to cut support?
Your best bet for this turn is probably supporting Rome to Venice with Adriatic Sea, and then convoying to Albania
I strongly encourage you to work with France against Germany right now
I really appreciate your support this turn.
That's really going to help me out, and I can then help you attack Austria

Why would you prefer me to work with France? I'm pretty useless against Germany, whereas France can take over the western half of the board quite easily, and you guys will be able to 3WD with whoever you wanted to later.
See I wasn't attacking you. Now how can I help you against Russia?
Yeah, that's my plan
Is there any chance you could move English Channel to London? That would stop Germany from taking the North Sea, and might make it easier for you to take the rest of England's centers
We should try to get Russia to flip on Austria here - they have a lot more to gain than Austria does if Russia is taking your centers
What do you think?
If you could not tap my units this turn, that would be a big help

Looks like you guys are able to carve up Italy pretty nicely.

Is there any chance you'll turn on Russia after this year? Italy and Turkey are basically dead, so there's not a lot of other places for your armies to go.
If you convoy to Albania I'll keep attacking you
It would be helpful if you could move an army into position to threaten Warsaw and/or Rumania
Any luck with Russia? I think they're going to grow way faster than Austria

Also, is there anything you could do to convince France to stop attacking me?

I think it's in both of your interests for France to fight Germany. Germany's a pretty easy 3WD, whereas France can actually take over the western half of the board.
Are you going to convoy Tunis to Albania?

If you continue to attack England, it will be much easier for Russia to stab Germany than for Russia to stab Austria. Your attack on England will only help Russia, and it will also let him move into position to stab Germany
Well you've basically declared war by putting a fleet in Greece and not moving out to Aegean
Do you think you could convince Germany to stab France?

Russia's not really my influence group, unfortunately.

I think you should go all in on an attack against Austria. They're probably going to give you some centers as Turkey dies.
I'll try
Aren't you going to lose Bulgaria?
It would also be helpful for me if you could tell me if you think Austria is willing to work with me, since I haven't been able to get Austria to stab Russia
Can you attack Con this turn to cut support?
I might need Mar to support Bur but if not I'll tap for you
If not, I need to know
I don't have much choice - I'm going to convoy to Albania
You should make peace with England and attack France
I'm sending messages to France and Germany telling them that attacking you will just let Russia get more centers, and that they should instead focus on Russia or Austria

I think you should attack Venice from Rome with support from the Adriatic, and convoy to Albania.

I think there's a decent chance that Russia and Austria will stab each other.
Hopefully that helps you a little bit
Why are you so hesitant to attack Austria? You are going to grow a lot more if you work with me than you are working with them
Do you want me to support Hel to North Sea again?
I have to move Serbia to Trieste
France's fleet in Irish Sea will also be helpful in taking out England

France is sort of ignoring me, unfortunately.

I think Russia might stab Austria - we'll see what happens this turn.

messages.message: I'll still help you take Bulgaria if you want
I'll vacate the North Sea this turn, for what it's worth.
Still attacking me, huh? I don't understand why you're working with Russia instead of me
Sorry about Constantinople

I'm going to support Albania to Greece and move Smyrna to Constantinople. If you want Bulgaria, you're going to have to support Greece to Bulgaria with Constantinople, and then move Trieste to Serbia to cover it. You'll also want to move your army in Vienna to Budapest
Russia is going to continue to grow, and you're going to have to devote units to holding them back
Can you support Italy to Greece?
I'll take your help
Are you going to work with Germany? I think they might be able to help you survive
I'm not willing to help you or Austria until you stop attacking me
I can maybe help you with France if you want
I'm pretty busy fighting Italy but I should be able to devote 1 or 2 units to helping you
If you want my help, you'll need to vacate Armenia and the Black Sea
Or actually, I guess I could use the North Sea to force the Channel.
Do you think you'll be able to retake Belgium?
I can help you turn on Russia if you want to do that
Alright you're right

Russia is really vulnerable right now, so you have a lot of potential for taking his centers. He's going to eventually take all of my centers, so you need to be prepared to attack him before he has a chance to attack you
We need to convince France that Austria and Russia are going to work together to wipe us all out. Please try to make that point to them
I'm open to any ideas - I just want to keep two centers.
I can't afford to stab Austria unless you help me. Otherwise, I'll just be killed by Austria later
Or convince Austria to flip on Russia, which is what I've been trying to do all game
But not at the cost of letting Russia or Germany take my centers.
Yes, if I can get Nth, I can support a move into Bel.
What's the plan this turn?

I'm trying to hold them off as long as I can, but I'm not going to last long without your help. They've already got 3 fleets down here, and more are coming - they're going to get most of my centers and then turn on you
France has been ignoring my messages, so I don't have any hopes of working with them.
I think you need to start making peace with Germany and start working with them against Russia and Austria
I think you need to help Russia solo, actually. At this point, Austria is not going to turn on Russia, and I don't have a way to survive.

It would also be helpful for me if you could get Austria to move against Russia now, before Russia is able to get more of my centers, or before Russia can move units west to threaten you. Russia is already in position to attack you, and your centers are going to be his next targets
I need to get some of my armies to fight Italy
I'm moving out of Bulgaria this turn. What do you want me to do?
So, I'm thinking I'll try to get into the Channel from North Sea. Then, I can do whatever is most helpful to you in the fall.
We could also try to take Smyrna. It's likely that Turkey is going to use Smyrna to try to take Con this turn
You can force North Sea this turn if you want, for what it's worth.
I'll turn on Russia if you move out of Albania
Any luck?
Could you support Bur-Mar? That should cause some confusion with F
It's important that you move Hel to North Sea, so that I can move Norway to Norwegian Sea
I'm going to move Piedmont to Tuscany to fight Italy
Take Greece this turn and try to defend Rome, for what it's worth.
I understand
Please do not move to Piedmont
You should also see if Germany will support you to English Channel

Russia's fleets are stuck in the north, so he doesn't have any units to stab you with, so you should be safe until Russia starts to build more fleets. Russia will definitely attack you once he has some builds
I will move it
They're saying they want to attack Russia, but I don't believe them. I think they're going to just keep attacking me and then go for the solo
Russia is getting out of control, we need to work together to contain them.
Is there any way you and Germany can work together against France?
Russia is going to have 9 units and Austria has 3 once I'm dead, and then they're going to turn on you. You need to make peace with France ASAP and attack Russia
What are you going to try to do this turn?
Once you move your units away from Armenia, I will be willing to help you against Austria
For what it's worth, I'm trying to convince Italy to attack Greece from Albania with support from the Ionian.
The army in Moscow instead of Warsaw is really good news for you, but they're about to turn on you soon
Is Turkey going to help you?
You might be able to coordinate with Italy. It's not like they have anything else to do with that unit.
Or do you have time to fight russia yet?
Russia is also in a good position to stab you now, since he can move his army in Finland to Sweden and his new army in Moscow to Warsaw
I'm going to try to take Greece
Yeah, I'm working with Germany against France.
Deal?
I really need your help, and you need me to do well enough that Austria won't turn on you when I'm dead
What do you think? AR is getting huge we can't keep fighting like this.
I'm sending fleets to help you take the rest of England's centers
Are you planning on turning on Russia any time soon?
It would be great if you moved Liverpool to Clyde or NAO
I'm not going to leave Albania until you actually start attacking Russia.
I can try to take a center from Russia if that would help you
I agree, I will move Bur - Mun
You should offer to help France attack Germany and take back Liverpool

You should be able to take Greece this turn if you use your army in Albania to move there with support from the Ionian Sea. You might also want to have your army in Rome move to Venice to cut support from a potential attack on Rome.
If you support yourself into Greece you'll take it
Are you moving from Albania?
Do you want me to encourage Austria to make moves to turn on Russia? Or are you just giving up at this point?
You can have Bel, but I'd like to get a center in England
Okay, let's finish England this year and turn to the line.

Also, I'm going to mute France if they keep ignoring me.

Sorry.
I'm happy to vacate Armenia if you help Italy take Greece. You could even ask Italy if they're willing to support you in, since they can't do anything else with that unit
I'm going to take Greece with Albania
I would appreciate it if you encouraged Austria to attack Russia
Sure, do you want support into NTH?
Yes
You might also want to mute Germany if he refuses to work with you
Can you move Pie-tus and Tyrolia-pie?
which unit?
Hel
What are you planning to do with English Channel?
You should attack Austria this year - I think you're going to be able to get a solo victory out of this game.
I'll support you into Greece, although I might be tapped by Russia
I'll move against Russia
Okay, I'm moving my armies as well
Okay order in.
What are you planning to do?
Also, how soon are you planning to turn on Russia?
what do you want me to do with it?
Please help!
If you don't want to work with me, you can just let Russia take all of my centers and then continue to attack Italy, but that would be a really boring path to take
If you take London this year, I will stab Germany next year to help you
I'm trying to convince Austria to turn around
You should take Burgundy and then Germany would have to destroy an army
I think you should tap Constantinople with Smyrna
Do you accept that?
Russia is going to move Bulgaria to Con with support from Black Sea

messages.message: Do you have any communication with France?
You should have your army in Apulia move to Rome and your fleet in the Ionian Sea support your army in Greece. I think that's the only way that you can defend all of your home centers this turn
Let me know if you want me to help you take Bulgaria this turn
Do you want me to move out of Bulgaria or do you want to take Con?
I'm going to have to use my fleet in the Aegean Sea to help defend my home centers
Or if you'd rather help me take it. It looks like Austria has turned on you now, so I would help you hurt them if you're willing
I want you to move out of Bulgaria, but I'm not sure how I'll be able to take Constantinople unless Russia vacates it
Sorry about the stab
I would like you to have your fleet in Bulgaria support my army in Smyrna to Constantinople
None, but they're finally sending units after Austria, so that's good. I still think it's too late though
If you agree to use Aegean to support Rumania to Bulgaria, I will stop attacking you
You might also want to move Trieste to Budapest and Galicia to Rumania
I was tapping Ruh to guarantee the move to Bur, I'll move Ruh out now, was not planning to end up there.
You should still offer to help Germany attack France. You can offer to send a unit into Brest or Belgium or something
You should have Edi.
They still ignore me.
I think you should try to take Constantinople with the Aegean Sea. Austria might support hold Bulgaria
I'm not going to help you until you move your units away from me. I'm not going to help you until you have to attack Austria on your own
Can you support Rumania to Bulgaria?
Please move back out of Piedmont
You are in the position to attack Austria now, so I'm willing to help you if you move your units away from my home centers
And yeah, that's what I'm going to do. I'm also going to try to support hold Greece with Ionian.
You could also try to retake Venice, but I don't think that's going to work
okay sounds good

I think that you should try to work with France at this point, since Germany is going to be able to take Edi from you this turn, and I don't think that France wants Germany to take all of your centers
Do you think England could help you against France?
Do you want me to do anything?
It looks like your stab has backfired. I'm going to retake Bulgaria this turn.
I think you should try to work with Germany against France
No, they're going to lose this year
France is a bigger threat than Germany
Maybe you can support Hol-Nth?
Do you want me to do anything? I'm trying to help you against France, which is in my best interests.
Russia will move Con to Bulgaria with support from the Black Sea
I think England is going to move English Channel to Belgium this turn, so you should support Brest to English Channel with MAO
Thanks for sending the unit to help. Do you think you could move it to Tyrolia?
I'm going to try to take Edi this turn
Nice move getting Greece
France is going to solo at this point, though. It's pretty much France + Russia v. you, and France can't really be stopped.
You and Germany need to make peace and start working together against Russia. They are growing way too fast
I did not expect France to move with me or I would move my armies to Warsaw
Now they're kinda stuck defending
Can you confirm that you will do that?
Turkey will move to Con with support from Smyrna
Thanks! I guess you're finally going to stop lying to me
We are
Could you try to move Denmark to Sweden?
You're not going to be able to take Warsaw, Rumania or Sevastopol this turn
I think this is a good time to attack Russia. I'll hold Greece and I think you should attack Rumania.
Sure
I'll also support Bulgaria to hold. I'd like to keep Greece, but I will let you have that back once you attack Russia
I have to focus on Russia
I think R might make a play for Edi. I can put you into Lon if you want.
I'm going to take Edi. It would be great if you could get Belgium this turn.
so you can build an army in Ber.
France might still work with you if you make the right offer
Okay.
Do you want any help against Germany?
I'm going to support hold Bulgaria too. I think this will help us hold back Russia. You should try to take Constantinople with Aegean with support from Smyrna
What are you trying to do this turn?
You really need to coordinate with Italy and Turkey to stop Russia.
I don't want to lose another center to Russia
You should try to move to Belgium
order in, also I am pulling back from Ruh.
France is clearly the bigger threat to you. Offer to help them attack Germany or something. They might give you Liverpool back in exchange
Yeah, R just told me they're taking Edi
Why did you force ENG? now you've lost Edi for sure.
I really want to focus on fighting Russia
France isn't talking to me.
Okay, I'll take Lon for now
Is England willing to support you to Belgium?
I'm not sure what to do.
I think you should work with England as well. They're going to lose Edinburgh this turn, and I think you should let them retake Liverpool. Then you can use the build to attack Germany
I guess it doesn't really matter if you retake Bulgaria, Italy is going to support Greece
Can you confirm that you'll use Greece to support Rumania to Bulgaria?
Actually, I'm going to support hold Bulgaria too. I don't want Russia to get another build.
You might have a chance if you guess right on France's moves
I will attack Serbia so you can take Bulgaria
Italy will support Greece so I won't be able to move out
You can fight R, I'll give you space but with all your armies in Italy it's hard to pull Pie back but it's no threat to you.
You might also want to try to take Belgium this turn
No
Do you think I should offer to support Austria into Rome, or should I try to bounce them again?
If you don't take Belgium, it's possible that France could take Munich this turn
If you move Greece to Serbia it would help me defend Bulgaria
I don't think they care much
I needed ENG if I was going to do anything.
You should also move Denmark to North Sea, so that you can take London later
I am protecting Munich
Yeah, I'll try for Belgium.
Never mind
I'm willing to stop attacking you next year if you help me take Bulgaria
If you move Piedmont to Tyrolia, it would be a huge problem for me and I might have to switch sides and help Germany

messages.message: I'll help you take Greece if you let me take back Constantinople

Russia is going to take back Rumania
I'm sorry that I stabbed you last turn, but I didn't want to risk Austria getting all of your centers
