Just so you know, I've accepted my defeat and I've accepted that you've lied to me all game. But I'm going to help Russia against you until you stop lying to me.
I'm willing to help you survive, but I won't give back Con this turn
I guess I was wrong about Russia
Could you move Piedmont to Marseilles?
Are you finally going to attack Russia?
Do you want to work together again, or are you committed to fighting me?
You're also in an amazing position to take Norway and Sweden

it's not going to tyr
I'm still willing to work with you, but you'll have to give Rumania back if you want that
You need to make sure that Russia doesn't get another army into Rumania. You should have your army in Vienna move to Galicia this turn
Would you be willing to help me against Russia if I could help you take Con and Ankara back?
I think you should let me retake my home centers and then I will help you against Russia.
There's not much we can do to coordinate our moves at this point, so I just ask that you make sure that you don't lose both of your home centers
I still have three units and I'm willing to help you if you let me take my home centers back
Sorry about the lies
I would also recommend moving your fleet in Trieste to the Adriatic Sea this turn
What are you trying to do this turn?
It's part of the game
I think there's a chance we can take Greece or Bulgaria in the fall.
Especially if Russia and Austria keep fighting each other
Thanks for sending the unit to help. Are you going to move it to Tyrolia?
Are you still willing to help me against Austria?
Please
And finally, I recommend moving Mid-atlantic to North Atlantic.
You need to have your army in Serbia support Rumania to hold and have your army in Budapest support Rumania to hold as well
I want to retake my home centers first, but once I have them back, I will be happy to work with you against Austria.
Why did you build in Berlin?

I'm going to continue to let you attack Austria unopposed as long as you don't move back to take my home centers. You're actually in an even better position to attack Austria now than you were last turn, so I recommend moving your units accordingly
How about you give me Bulgaria and I give you back Rumania?
Are you still willing to work together?
Your fleet in Greece also needs to tap Bulgaria to make sure that you don't lose Rumania
Would that work?
You should move Apu to Nap and Ion to Adr
Are you still with me against Russia?
I'm willing to work with you against Germany
We have to work together to stop Russia
You're not going to be able to fight Russia and defeat me at the same time. And I'm very motivated to help Russia attack you.
Would you let me retreat into Bulgaria?
If you don't answer me, I'm going to assume that you're going to attack me
I will also be tapping Constantinople with my fleet in the Aegean Sea, so there's a chance that you can take Bulgaria this turn
I'm not going to move to Adriatic Sea. I need to support Apulia to Naples.
Also, I would prefer if you didn't move into Galicia
Are you going to keep the fleet in the Aegean Sea alive?
If you do move your units to attack Austria, I will also work with you
We should have a truce in England. You should convoy Picardy to Wales, so that you can take London later.
Russia will move Norway to Sweden
Your moves are extremely important this turn. I hope that you have them entered correctly
I'm also very confident that Germany is going to start attacking Russia.

Austria is planning on having Greece support Rumania to Bulgaria and moving Vienna to Galicia this turn. I strongly recommend you not allow Austria to take Bulgaria this turn. You also need to support Bulgaria to Rumania with both Sevastopol and the Black Sea to ensure that you take it
Do you think you could move Mid-atlantic to North Atlantic?
If you attack me, I'm going to let France take all of your centers
Hi, the chat wasn't working
Thanks, I can move Den a bit differently then
Would you want to convoy to Yor?
Thanks for the help. Yeah, I have everything entered
Why don't you move your army in Apulia to Naples and your fleet in the Ionian Sea to the Adriatic Sea?
Ber was my only center on which I could build btw
You could also just hold
I think I should use the Ionian to support Apu to Nap
I'll let you keep Tunis
Sure that would work out well to push R off the island.
I can't retake Rumania this turn, so I don't agree to that
I'll use Ionian to help you fight Austria next turn. For now, I need to defend myself against them
I'd rather just fight you
I'm going to help Russia attack you unless you stop attacking me
You're the biggest power so it would be hard to work together
Would you want to move Bel or Pic?
I think it's time to move against Russia
What are you planning to do with the army in Berlin?
Are we set with the Convoy?
Agreed
Munich to Silesia and Berlin to Prussia would help a lot
Yes, I'm doing that. What are your moves?
I think you should make peace with Germany and Austria. It's only going to help Russia to attack you
Which army should I convoy?
What are you planning to do this turn?
I'm not going to help you until you attack Russia on your own. I will continue to tap Constantinople though
I think you should move Wales back to Liverpool and use the rest of your fleets to attack Russia. They're the biggest threat right now
Bel, it will help us descalate too
Thanks, your help will be remembered
Okay, will Convoy Bel-Yor
You shouldn't have stabbed me, because now I'm not going to help you against Austria
Ok, I'm going to use my units to attack Austria this turn. I'm not going to let you retake Con or Ankara.
I would suggest that you move your army in Ankara to Smyrna
If you attack Germany, I will let Russia solo
It would take forever to get the units necessary to attack you
I would suggest that you support one of your units to Bulgaria. That way, you might be able to take Bulgaria and help me take Constantinople, which is a win-win
Ok, sounds good. I will probably be able to use your help next turn.

I think that you should just try to defend yourself at this point, because Austria has four units in Italy, and if you can get one of your units into the Adriatic Sea, then it will be a lot easier to defend
It also looks like France and Germany are going to work together against you, so you might want to move some of your units to defend your northern territories
Are you using Ionian Sea to support Apu to Nap? If you don't do this, Austria could support Rome to Nap and take it.
If you let me destroy your army, you can rebuild a fleet
It may help if you move your fleets around to NAO.
I would suggest that you move Bulgaria to Rumania with support from the Black Sea and Sevastapol, and move Constantinople to Bulgaria with support from the Black Sea
I'm coming to help you. could you support me in the next turn?
If you take Naples and Tunisia, I'm going to help Russia
I'm going to try to move Rumania to Bulgaria
Then we can set up a convoy to Scandinavia later. Or you can consider going to the mediterranean
You need to find a way to work with Germany against Russia. If you and Germany fight, then Russia will be able to solo
It seems like you don't want to work together.
It would be really bad if you attacked Germany right now and allowed Russia to get all of Germany's centers, since that would be a lot easier for Russia to solo than for you
Otherwise you'll be stuck on 1 center forever
You should consider convoying your army in Picardy to Wales this turn and moving Wales to Liverpool
I'm also telling you to watch out for France. If they take Tunisia, then they can send fleets into the Mediterranean to attack you
Can you tell me if you're going to move the army in Berlin to Prussia or Silesia?
Since I'm working with Austria vs Russia, we'll need to see that A doesn't get too strong
I'll use Ionian to support Apu to Naples. If I can get Austria to back off, I might still have a chance to stay in the game
I'm going to move Ankara to Smyrna this turn, so please block me.
I'm thinking of going to the med, I think you and I have enough to push R out of the north.
I'm moving to Galicia and trying to take Bulgaria
If you let me keep Tunis, I'll use that unit to help you attack Russia. That's my only chance to stay in the game. Otherwise, you'll just take Tunisia eventually
Berlin is moving to Kie
I would suggest that you have Belgium support Burgundy to hold, Picardy convoy to Wales and Wales move to Liverpool
You also have three units to help you take Bulgaria this turn
Swe is easy for you to take.
Also you would need to back off a bit to make this work

I hope so. I think Nwy-Swe this turn
So It'll be a guessing game later.

messages.message: I think Austria will move Ionian to Aegean this turn. If you bounce them there, I might be able to keep Naples for another year.
You can't break through
Can you move Tunis to Ionian Sea to cut Austria's support?
Maybe you could also use Naples to support France's army in Tuscany to Rome.
You just need to hold in Tunis now
I'm going to take Naples
If I move to Ionian, Austria will just take Naples
I would've liked you support my move to War, but I'll move into a better position this year
Austria is a bigger threat to you than I am.
Let me know if you are planning an attack on Ukr
You could move Pie to Ven, Tuscany to Rome supported by Tyrrhenian Sea, and Western Med to Tunis to take two centers from Austria.
I will move to Ionian though. If you move to Aegean, you should be able to retake Bulgaria or Rumania this year
I need to support hold Rumania
Ok. Sorry that I didn't believe you when you said you were willing to let me keep Tunis if I didn't support France into Rome
I suggest that you move Prussia to Livonia
Why don't you want to work together?
Okay
If we keep fighting, Austria is going to become too strong
You were getting too strong
I want to work with you
can you help me take Rom from Austria from Tuc?
Yes, that's true.
Are you moving Constantinople to Aegean?
I'm going to retake Rumania. You can't defend it.
You need to defend your North
Yes. I'll use Naples to support Tuscany into Rome
Maybe we should stop fighting.
What can you offer me? I want the Italian centers or Tun and Rom.
I'm using Tunis to attack Ionian. If you support Tuscany into Rome with Tyrrhenian, you should be able to take Rome this turn
I'm not going to give you Rumania back
France wants me to support Tuscany into Rome. If you move Rome to Venice with support from Trieste, you should be able to keep Venice and keep France from taking Rome
Yes, I'm moving Con to Aegean Sea.
We can finish Italy quickly, then I'll move to attack Russia
France is also going to become too strong if you and Austria continue to attack me.
can you move Rom-Nap?
France has a lot of armies that are useless against Austria.
But if you take it I will ally with Germany against you
Austria can't defend against France's armies in Italy

sure

Can you help me take Norway next year?

Do you want to work with me now?

obvious

I'll probably move Tunis to Ionian, to cut support if Austria is using Ionian to support Naples into Tyrrhenian
I am open to helping you contain Russia, I may make a play for Tun

that sounds good to me.
